message.content: A Bombus vosnesenskii is a species of bumblebee commonly found in western North America. They are medium-sized bees with a furry, yellow and black striped body. The yellow stripes are thick, while the black stripes are narrow. The thorax is covered in short, dense hair that is yellowish-orange in color. They have a round head with large, black compound eyes and short antennae. Their wings are clear with a slightly yellowish tint. Bombus vosnesenskii are important pollinators for many plants, including fruit trees, berries, and wildflowers. They can be found in a variety of habitats, including meadows, forests, and gardens.
